reviews.title: Nice beach pavilion with nice lunch and nice staff
reviews.text:
Nice place, good food and very friendly staff. We hardly had to wait and enjoyed a “simple yet nutritious” meal with a great value for money. We don't understand the negative reviews... 
“Little understanding for noisy children” (raise them!) “little choice for difficult eaters” (who is it?) .  So we say just do it and enjoy it. And no, we don’t have any shares 😉

reviews.title: Beautiful view directly on the beach of Harlingen
reviews.text:
Nicely located restaurant right on the beach of Harlingen. The service was very friendly😊.
Aperol Spritz for 9,50€ - large glass, unfortunately too little Aperol, Prosecco tasted strongly of wood - of course a matter of taste :) in addition there are small snacks, soups and other dishes.

reviews.title: Dinner party Harlingen
reviews.text:
Delicious food in a beautiful place on the water! They just built a new terrace.
Staff are friendly and the food the shortrib and salmon were superb! 
For a beach bar just a good restaurant with good food!!

reviews.title: Things not in order, disappointing
reviews.text: Unfortunately disappointing visit. The location is beautiful but otherwise you should not be at salt. The service is very busy especially with itself. They stand chatting at the bar with their backs to guests, take time to eat at rush hour and sit extensively at the regular table on a laptop while guests are not served. It's a long time before you can finally get the attention. Then you ask for menu and it is not brought. Waiting again. Eventually ordered, tea, cake and a soup. After we had long had the tea and my husband's cake, my soup had not yet come. We just left then. At checkout, of course, the soup was on the receipt. We said he didn't come. Oh was said and without further apology or whatever the soup was pulled off and we paid. What a terrible unprofessional state of affairs. If they want to make money out of this place, I'd first make sure they put things in order and train some better staff. They won't see us again.

reviews.title: Just enjoy the coast.
reviews.text:
Great lunch for a great price. 
A small menu with tasty dishes. We chose a goat cheese sandwich and a goat cheese sandwich.

reviews.title: Bwoa
reviews.text: Service not so friendly, little tolerant to kids who make noise, nice that the menu is limited but to be a beach pavilion little fish.

reviews.title: Moderate
reviews.text: It took a long time. And for difficult eaters, there aren't really any options on the menu. Well nice staff and the food was also tasty it only took gwn long

reviews.title: One-time
reviews.text: Fine for fresh fish. The fried fish leaves something to be desired. Also the restaurant itself does not look very fresh sticky tables and ditto plastic chairs are not very inviting

reviews.title: It was great again!
reviews.text:
Stands out because of the owner's excellent memory...still knows us from 1 visit per year.
Reserves a sea bass especially for us. See you next year...Renee and Frits

reviews.title: This really isn't possible
reviews.text:
The place is beautiful to sit.
However, when you place an order and you wait half an hour to hear: I have a disappointing message, the salmon you ordered is still frozen.
There are still areas for improvement in terms of organization for insight and overview in the kitchen!!!!
There we were waiting for a rosé and beer. No apology or gesture from here, just a few bitterballen for the inconvenience. As a customer you think I will order something else. Customer loyalty and friendly treatment is a concept that needs more work. We paid for our drink and left, also showing no interest in paying.

reviews.title: Nice location!
reviews.text: Nice location on the beach. Good food too! Unfortunately our waitress was not that friendly/grumpy.

reviews.title: Bad cuisine
reviews.text:
What a bad kitchen!
The potatoes and grilled vegetables floated out of the pan with fat. There were no options for people with (gluten) allergies and putting together a suitable dish was difficult. The food took a long time to arrive, the price/quality ratio was completely out of proportion!
The place is beautiful but that's about it... what a shame!

reviews.title: Just moved to Harlingen and after mediocre first visit to Zilt, I wanted to give it another go.
reviews.text: First, I had to send coffee back as it tasted off (like old milk or so) but waitress said the machine was wrong. Then in full anticipation I ordered my sandwich with goat cheese and Figs but this sandwich is the saddest looking and saddest tasting sandwich ever. For €10.50 its really below mediocre. My 8 year old son can do better. I hope the place can sort out their staff out. Beside the food the places doesn't show much ambiance; it's old and tired looking. Unfortunately there's no competition on that side of town. This was my 2 visit, after my first one was mediocre. I won't return again I'm afraid😟

reviews.title: Location, location, location or not?
reviews.text:
I hope the experience was a one off and that this place does not think it can rely only on Location as its USP. 
The order was messed up. 
The service rude.
The toilets were disgusting. 
While it is undersatandable there has just been a pandemic, it would be wise to make sure staff are trained and happy. I will be using this place as a case study for my hospitality students at university on how not to run a place. I hope the owner takes note of all the other reviews too. 
The Harlingen Gemeente will be getting a copy of this.

reviews.title: Good sunset food
reviews.text: Great fresh quality food. Great staff, great location with a splendid view over the Waddenzee and the harbor of Harlingen

reviews.title: A great view but consistently indifferent service
reviews.text:
We have visited Harlingen many times over the last 3 years and on our last visit we decided to have lunch at ’t Zilt to see if it had improved, however, this was not the case. In fact it had deteriorated even further than our prior visits.
We walked in and sat down inside with no acknowledgement at all from any of the staff and we waited for some table service and guess what none came. We sat for at least 15 minutes and still no service. 
We made the decision that we would not reward this cafe with our patronage so we got up from our table and walked out and again we were not approached by any staff as we walked out. The food has never been very good here, however the view is amazing and it is most enjoyable to have a drink on the deck overlooking the Wadden Sea.
Our final impression was one of great customer indifference which was disappointing to say the least.

reviews.title: "Close call"
reviews.text:
The view is Fantastic, but we orded the food but had to wait for more then 40 minutes for our food, but the food was "Excellent" . But we almost left the restaurant.
But afterall our evening ended with a positive feeling.

reviews.title: Fantastic place near the harbour of Harlingen
reviews.text: I visited Strandpaviljoen "t Zilt many times. Every time I visit Friesland I try to get there  to experience the very nice atmosphere and enjoy the view on the sea. The food is nice, the staff is friendly. It is simply a place you keep in mind and would like to enjoy more than once.

reviews.title: Casual Bar at the Beach
reviews.text: It is a casual bar at the beach in Harlingen. The menu consists of a classic choice of food. We had a nice seat outside with a view on the sea. For Lunch we got sandwiches with pesto, mozzarella and tomato. It was fresh and tasty and not expensive. So, no complaints.

reviews.title: Nice view and good food
reviews.text: Great place to sit and relax during the summer. Lot's of variety on the menu. The food and drinks are not expensive and are of good quality. We had no problems and would recommend this place.

reviews.title: Stunning view and sun down. Also good food
reviews.text:
Their menu is rather basic, but what hey serve tastes really good. 

The price for the food is okay when you take into account the great view you have on the Waddensea from their terrace.

reviews.title: Excellent location, good food, bad service...
reviews.text:
It's really a lovely place to sit and have a drink, or even something to eat (quite pricey though), as long as you're not too hungry (or thirsty) and have some time to spare because the service is well, crap. 

When I went there for dinner with friends, it took forever to get something to drink but then they never returned to ask our orders. We waited for I believe over an hour and then we decided to leave. In the meantime I also wanted to ask something but before I had the chance to even open my mouth, the guy said I had to ask his colleague because (and I quote) 'he didn't know anything'... 

I have since returned (because I was invited by people and well, the location really is excellent - right on the seaside and they have a great terrace), but that time the service was ridiculously slow as well. Food was descent though (be it, like I mentioned before, pricey).
